Description: Body sherd of North Ionian pottery bowl; interior glazed (fired dark brown), with two added red bands, and probably some added white; exterior: band between reserved areas; inscription on exterior.
Bibliographic references: Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (pl. 23.1.20)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.250)
